            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Possible addition to the auto-assigned namespace: `vim.notify` calls.\n\nI think many plugins have a function similar to this:\n\n```lua\nlocal function show_msg(msg, lvl)\n  vim.notify(\"my-plugin: \" .. msg, lvl, {})\nend\n```\n\nWould be nice to use `vim.notify` in your plugin and have it autoprefixed with the plugin name, or by setting some metadata on the notification with the name of the plugin?",
