            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Prefixing all messages with the plugin name will raise some difficult (back-compat) questions, but at minimum we certainly will set a `source` field or something like that on all messages emitted by any plugin.\n\nAnd then we can consider adding a parameter to `nvim_echo` which automatically prefixes the plugin name. Maybe also a global option.\n\n`vim.notify` itself is just not relevant will be deprecated eventually. It was a half-measure that did not address things at the core level (i.e. in the messages subsystem).",
